body:
Prefix module pass can create duplicate copies of a module and rename them, the renaming depends on the instantiating context. 
Duplicating a module based on the context, can invalidate some of the `NonLocalAnchor` symbols on the `InstanceOp`. 
This PR checks for the module path of the `firrtl.nla` and removes the invalid symbols.
The Prefix module pass traverses the instance graph in a top down order, hence all the instance ops in the parent module are fixed before moving on to the children.
While iterating over all the `InstanceOp`s of any module, it should be sufficient to check that the module path of the `firrtl.nla` contains the current module and the module being instantiated. Otherwise the `nla` can be dropped from the instance op.

In the following example, if `@Mod2` is duplicated, one instantiated from `@Top` and the other from `@Mod1`,  
then only one of the `firrtl.nla` is valid in each copy.
`firrtl.nla @nla_0 [@Top, @Mod1, @Mod2, @Mod3]`
`firrtl.nla @nla_1 [@Top, @Mod2, @Mod3]`
Hierarchy representation:
```
Top - Mod1 - Mod2 - Mod3
  | 
Mod2 - Mod3  
```
Before Prefix:
   ```

  firrtl.nla @nla_0 [@Top, @Mod1, @Mod2, @Mod3] ["t_a", "a_b", "b_z", "x"]
  firrtl.nla @nla_1 [@Top, @Mod2, @Mod3] ["t_b", "b_z", "x"]
  firrtl.module @Top() {
    firrtl.instance t_a {annotations = [{circt.nonlocal = @nla_0, class = "circt.nonlocal"}]} @Mod1()
    firrtl.instance t_b {annotations = [{circt.nonlocal = @nla_1, class = "circt.nonlocal"}]} @Mod2()
  }
  firrtl.module @Mod1()
    attributes {annotations = [{
      class = "sifive.enterprise.firrtl.NestedPrefixModulesAnnotation",
      prefix = "XXX_",
      inclusive = false
    }]} {
    firrtl.instance a_b {annotations = [{circt.nonlocal = @nla_0, class = "circt.nonlocal"}]} @Mod2()
  }
  firrtl.module @Mod2() {
    firrtl.instance b_z {annotations = [
        {circt.nonlocal = @nla_0, class = "circt.nonlocal"},
        {circt.nonlocal = @nla_1, class = "circt.nonlocal"}
      ]} @Mod3()
  }
  firrtl.module @Mod3() { }

```
After prefix modules:
```
    firrtl.nla @nla_0 [@Top, @Mod1, @XXX_Mod2, @XXX_Mod3] ["t_a", "a_b", "b_z", "x"]
    firrtl.nla @nla_1 [@Top, @Mod2, @Mod3] ["t_b", "b_z", "x"]
    firrtl.module @Top() {
      firrtl.instance t_a  {annotations = [{circt.nonlocal = @nla_0, class = "circt.nonlocal"}]} @Mod1()
      firrtl.instance t_b  {annotations = [{circt.nonlocal = @nla_1, class = "circt.nonlocal"}]} @Mod2()
    }
    firrtl.module @Mod1() {
      firrtl.instance a_b  {annotations = [{circt.nonlocal = @nla_0, class = "circt.nonlocal"}]} @XXX_Mod2()
    }
    firrtl.module @Mod2() {
      firrtl.instance b_z  {annotations = [{circt.nonlocal = @nla_1, class = "circt.nonlocal"}]} @Mod3()
    }
    firrtl.module @XXX_Mod2() {
      firrtl.instance b_z  {annotations = [{circt.nonlocal = @nla_0, class = "circt.nonlocal"}]} @XXX_Mod3()
    }
    firrtl.module @XXX_Mod3() {    }
    firrtl.module @Mod3() {    }
 
```
